The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Atapattu stays captain

Colombo: Sri Lanka have reappointed Maravan Atapattu as Test and one-day captain for their series against the West Indies and India. 

Sri Lanka are due to play a two-match Test series against the West Indies starting on July 15, and a seven-match tri-series involving India from August 1. The dates and venues are still to be confirmed. 

The reappointment of Atapattu was ratified by the sports minister. (AGENCIES) 




